<HEADLINE> Death Toll in Kashmir Blast Goes Up to 11 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
While 7 people were killed on the spot, 4 others succumbed to
injuries in hospitals, said the PTI.
</P>
<P>
Former Jammu and Kashmir minister Maulvi Iftikhar Hussain
Ansari, who was believed to be the main target of the attack and
was among the 11 injured in the blast, was stated to be out of
danger, the PTI reported.
</P>
<P>
No militant outfit has claimed responsibility for the blast,
the PTI added. 
</P>
