<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodia Back on fast Track of Sustainable Economic Growth: Hun Sen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Prime Minister Hun Sen
staged a vigorous investment promotion Friday by affirming to
Singapore business community that Cambodia is back on the fast
track of sustainable economic growth and time is ripe for them to
invest in his country.
</P>
<P>
"AS Cambodia is back on the fast track of sustainable economic
growth testified by encouraging achievements during the past year,
I am confident that it is the right time for the business
community and investors to make a thorough assessment of Cambodia'
s potential and opportunities and work out a long-term vision for
the country." Hun Sen said in his address at the dinner hosted in
his honor by the Singapore Chinese Chamber of Commerce and
Industry.
</P>
<P>
Listing results achieved in 1999 by his government in
implementation of the "Triangle Strategy" put forward by himself,
Hun Sen said that his country's real GDP rose 4.3 percent in 1999
after plummeting to one percent in 1997 and 1998, the inflation
rate fell sharply to almost zero percent following a 12.6-percent
upsurge in 1998, the exchange rate was fairly stable ranging
around 3,800 riels per U.S. dollar and the international reserves
increased by eight percent covering 3.9 months of imports.
</P>
<P>
He also said that tourist arrivals are increasing exponentially
and exports grew rapidly thanks largely to the growing garment
industry which now employs over 100,000 people.
</P>
<P>
He said that Cambodia is expected to experience GDP growth of 5.
5 percent in 2000 and six percent in the years afterwards with
inflation kept under the five percent benchmark and the exchange
rate standing stable around 3,800 riels to one U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that his government's most important agenda is
rapid alleviation of the poverty and accelerating economic
progress building on hard, newly gained peace, stability and unity
of territory and goals agreed upon at the national level.
</P>
<P>
On the objectives of his government's development strategies,
he said the thrust targets to achieve long-term sustainable
economic growth at an annual rate of 6-7 percent, equitable
distribution of the fruits of economic growth between the haves
and have-nots and between urban and rural areas as well as between
the two sexes, and sustainable management and utilization of the
environment and natural resources.
</P>
<P>
Noting that his country needs financial resources to expand
production and create employment as well as technology, knowledge
and know-how to improve capacity and productivity, the prime
minister said that his government regards the private sector as an
engine of growth and promised to guarantee to all investors a
favorable environment conducive to investment, especially peace,
security, political and macroeconomic stability, efficient legal
and institutional framework, transparency, accountability and
predictability.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen is in Singapore on a three-day official visit and he
has held talks with his Singapore counterpart Goh Chok Tong, met
some other senior Singapore officials and toured Singapore port,
an estate of the Housing Development Board and an international
business park since his arrival on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
