<HEADLINE> Swedish Prime Minister to Mediate in Mideast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Swedish Prime Minister Goran
Persson will travel to the Middle East on Sunday for meetings with
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat and Israeli Prime Minister Ehud
Barak, Persson's office said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The office said Persson's visit was requested by the two
leaders.
</P>
<P>
Persson will first travel to the West Bank to meet Arafat, then
hold talks with Barak in Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Palestine and Israel held secret negotiations in Stockholm last
month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
