<DOCNO> XIE20000603.0011 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait Denies Life of Puppet PM Threatened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait on Saturday denied press
reports on its threat against the life of Alaa Hussein, captive
head of the short-lived Kuwaiti puppet regime established by Iraq
after its invasion of Kuwait in August 1990.
</P>
<P>
"The statements Alaa Hussein made to the London-based Arabic
daily Al Sharq Al Awsat are utterly baseless," said Colonel Hussein
Al-Abdessalam, director of rehabilitation institutes at Kuwait's
Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
A Kuwaiti court recently upheld the death sentence on Alaa
Hussein, who returned to Kuwait from Norway last January to appeal
the death sentence issued in 1991 on charges of high treason.
</P>
<P>
Alaa Hussein, who has been kept behind bars since his return,
has again appealed against the death sentence.
</P>
<P>
In a statement to Al Sharq Al Awsat published Saturday, Alaa
Hussein said his prison director warned that "I am under threat of
gunshot within the prison."
</P>
<P>
But Al-Abdessalam said special security measures are applied to
all those sentenced to death in order to safeguard their lives and
safety.
</P>
<P>
He said the prison department had dedicated Alaa Hussein a
solitary confinement until his legal procedures is completed.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
