<HEADLINE> IDB Could Reject Peru 400 Million Dollar Loan: Economist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Interamerican Development Bank (
IDB) could reject a Peruvian request for over 400 million U.S.
dollars in loans because of the political crisis it is undergoing,
economist Humberto Campodonico told the press Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The specialist said that this economic package is part of the
loans pending evaluation by the IDB executive officials and
programmed for disbursement this year.
</P>
<P>
Campodonico said that if the IDB does not approve these loans
for a total of more than 400 million dollars, the government of
President Alberto Fujimori, who was reelected on May 28 for a
third mandate, would be facing a serious problem of public works
financing for his new presidential period.
</P>
<P>
He said that if the IDB loans for road infrastructure do not
arrive, the creation of jobs and the entitlement of land for
agriculture would also be restricted.
</P>
<P>
The Peruvian government is expecting the resolution to be
adopted in the next days by the Organization of American States
and the U.S. government, to have access to credits by
international financial organizations, among them the IDB.
</P>
</TEXT>
