<HEADLINE> S. Africa Launches School Anti-Crime Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 3 (Xinhua) -- South African Justice Minister
Penuell Maduna launched on Saturday an anti-crime project in
schools named Strengthening Education, saying no government will
tolerate a situation where pupils are denied the opportunity to
learn because of criminal elements in schools
</P>
<P>
Maduna said situations like the rioting be avoided if parents
take a more active role in their children's schooling.
</P>
<P>
Maduna encouraged parents to take an active interest in their
children's education and activities at school.
</P>
<P>
"As a society we have the responsibility to weed out criminals
in our communities and schools," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Strengthening Education project is a Business Against Crime
 initiative to create safer school environments through character
building workshops and monitoring of violence and absenteeism in
schools.
</P>
<P>
The Centre for the Study of Violence and Reconciliation and
several non- governmental organizations as well as some
government bodies are involved in the project. 
