<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's Acting Transport and
Energy Minister Simon Moyo Saturday said the government is making
every effort to ensure the constant availability of fuel which
has been in short supply since the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
Moyo told the Zimbabwe News Agency that the government was
facing a lot of hitches in its efforts to procure fuel supplies,
but was doing everything possible to improve the situation.
</P>
<P>
