France has not made any decision on sending more troops to Lebanon
because the Lebanese government has not yet promised to deploy
government troops to control the border area with Israel.
</P>
<P>
United Nations Secretary General Kofi Annan has suggested the
expansion of the United Nations Interim Force in Lebanon (UNIFIL)
from 4,500 to 7,900 after Israel pulled out its troops from
southern Lebanon last month.
</P>
<P>
France has 250 troops in the UNIFIL, which was deployed by the
U.N. in Lebanon in 1978. 
