<HEADLINE> Galanz Increases Micro-Wave Oven Exports to Europe and America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The world's leading micro-wave oven
producer, Galanz, announced here today that it has received export
orders up to 8 million units for this year. Ninety percent of them
came from Europe and America.
</P>
<P>
Exports will account for 67 percent of Galanz's output target
this year, which stands at 12 million units. The company earns
over 100 million U.S. dollars in foreign exchange annually from
exports.
</P>
<P>
Galanz, which has grown up from a township company in Shunde,
Guangdong Province in south China, is targeting high-quality home
appliance markets in Europe and America.
</P>
<P>
Its research center, based in America, has developed technology
for producing a number of the world's most advanced micro-wave
oven products including intelligent remote-control ovens, sound-
control and Internet-controlled ovens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
