<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seismologists Urge to Enhance Cross-Straits Academic Exchanges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Academic exchanges across the Taiwan
Straits should be intensified to provide more effective guidelines
for practical anti-earthquake work, said seismologists attending a
seismological symposium here today.
</P>
<P>
He Yongnian, director of the Seismological Technological
Exchange Center, called for more flexible, comprehensive and
effective ways to promote cross-Straits academic exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Seismologists from Taiwan said that seismological exchanges
have been enhanced since September 21, 1999 when Taiwan was hit by
a terrible earthquake. He also suggested that long-term exchange
visits should be considered.
</P>
<P>
According to He, three seismological symposiums have been held
since 1992. The fourth one is expected to be hosted in Taipei in
October or November this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
