<HEADLINE> Inland Municipality Streamlines Rules to Draw Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing Municipality in
southwest China abolished 44 licenses and approval requirements
and 76 items of compulsory payments of companies so as to
encourage businesses and individuals to invest in this southwest
China industrial heartland.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing Mayor Bao Xuding said here today that the municipal
government will abolish all local regulations that run
contradictory to the central government's policy to accelerate the
development of western China.
</P>
<P>
The city has also cut links between 207 intermediate agents and
their former government sponsors. These agents include accounting,
auditing and taxation offices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
