<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Upset by Hong Kong in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 3 (Xinhua) -- South China from Hong Kong SAR
scored an upset here on Saturday by stunning powerhouse Yugoslavia
's national team 4-2 in a soccer friendly.
</P>
<P>
The local hosts unleashed a string of pressure on the visitors'
defense, especially in the first half, and made sound use of their
attempts.
</P>
<P>
Four minutes into the game, forward Zeljko Gavrilovic of
Yugoslavia opened the account for the Hong Kong club by rubbing a
pass from Lee Kim Wo, and added one more 21 minutes later by
rushing into the box after catching a long pass.
</P>
<P>
As the hosts kept attacking, Lee Kim Wo delivered a delicate
pass to captain Cheng Siu Chung, who left-footed the ball into the
net for a comfortable 3-0 margin.
</P>
<P>
To prevent its first line-ups from injury for the up-coming
European Championship a week later, Yugoslavia substituted seven
players and striker Mateja Kezman broke his team's deadlock by
heading home in the 66th minute.
</P>
<P>
Yet, the hosts were in high spirit and defender Lee Wai Tik
slammed home outside the box three minutes later, dampening any
winning hope for the visitors.
</P>
<P>
Although it netted again through a free kick in the 90th minute,
Yugoslavia still suffered its first defeat in its Asian tour after
a 2-0 over China one week ago, and two goalless ties against South
Korea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
