BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Two Japanese master flower
arrangers taught Chinese visitors "ikebana", or the art of
arranging flowers, at a demonstration held in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
The demonstration was hosted by Beijing Municipal Association
for Friendship With Foreign Countries and a Japanese corporation.
Two hundred florists from north China attended the event.
</P>
<P>
While briefing Chinese audience on general artistic style and
trends now popular in the world in arranging flowers, the two
Japanese masters also showed them how to arrange flowers for
occasions such as weddings and meetings.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that annual sales of flowers has risen by 35
percent in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
