<HEADLINE> Singapore Prime Minister to Visit Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok
Tong will visit Ireland, Belgium and Germany from June 5 to 16 to
strengthen and expand bilateral cooperation between his country
and the three European countries, Singapore Prime Minister's
Office announced in a press statement Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In the three countries, the prime minister will meet his
counterparts to discuss means to strengthen and expand bilateral
cooperation as well as to exchange views with them on regional and
global developments including Asia-Europe relations, the statement
says.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister will also take this opportunity to meet top
businessmen and industrialists, academics, journalists and opinion-
makers in the various countries, the statement adds.
</P>
<P>
Singapore Minister for Foreign Affairs and Law S. Jayakumar,
parliament member Wang Kai Yuen and senior officials from the
Ministry of Foreign Affairs will accompany the prime minister in
the visit which will take him to the cities of Dublin, Brussels,
Berlin, Munich and Stuttgart.
</P>
<P>
Also on his agenda are visits to the Inter-University Micro-
Electronics Center in Belgium, the largest independent micro-
electronics research and development center in Europe, Martinsried
in Munich, an incubator for bio-technology industries, and the
Daimler-Chrysler Headquarters in Stuttgart.
</P>
<P>
During his absence, the acting prime minister will be Deputy
Prime Minister Tony Tan from June 4-6, Minister for Finance
Richard Hu from June 7 to 10 and Deputy Prime Minister Lee Hsien
Loong from June 11 to 17.
</P>
</TEXT>
