<HEADLINE> Strong Quake Hits Eastern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 3 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake measuring 5.8 on
the open-ended Richter scale jolted eastern Japan on Saturday
afternoon, the Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of casualties or damage and no
tsunami or tidal wave warning was issued.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake, which occurred at 5:54 p.m. local
time (0854 GMT), was estimated to be about 50 kilometers
underground in the northeastern part of Chiba Prefecture, east of
Tokyo, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
The quake was also strongly felt in Tokyo and Ibaraki
Prefecture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
