<DOCNO> XIE20000603.0097 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Number of Refugees in Uganda Amounts to 200,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Uganda currently has 200,000
refugees who have entered the east African country from its
neighbors, the Monitor daily reported here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"The largest number is from Sudan totalling 185,000, while
others are from Kenya, Ethiopia, Eritrea and the Democratic
Republic of the Congo," representative of the United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees Saihou Saidy was quoted by the paper as
saying at the opening of a two-day annual workshop for refugees
and human rights activists in Uganda Friday.
</P>
<P>
The workshop was organized by the Sudan Human Rights
Association (SHRA).
</P>
<P>
Secretary General of SHRA Mohamed Abdelrhman Salih said that
since the insurgency resumed in Sudan in 1983, about 2 million
Sudanese have lost lives, over 4.5 million are internally
displaced and over 1 million are living in exile. 
</P>
</TEXT>
