<HEADLINE> Denmark to Provide Aid to Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Danish government will
provide Nepal with financial assistance amounting to 143 million U.
S.dollars over the next five years for development projects in the
country, according to the Nepali Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said in a release here Saturday that the aid was
announced by the Danish Foreign Ministry during the annual
consultations on bilateral development cooperation between Nepal
and Denmark which ended here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Danish assistance to Nepal will focus on the four areas of
basic and primary education, energy, natural resource management
and the environment.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the agreed strategy for Danish-Nepalese
development cooperation, support for good governance and
decentralization is also a major aspect of the cooperation program.
</P>
<P>
Nepal is one of the 20 priority countries for Danish
development assistance. 
</P>
