But I will feel terribly sorry if China does not take part in this
tournament. China has been absent for three years and I think the
tournament is not complete without the Chinese shuttlers. It's not
like the All England or Thomas Cup, which are attended by teams
from all over the globe," he was quoted by the Jakarta Post
Saturday as saying.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old Taufik said he wished he could meet world top
ranking player Peter Gade Christensen of Denmark in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
"I have played Peter Gade many times, but I could only beat him
in the Singapore Open last August. I'm still expecting to fight
him even though I've lost to him in most of our meetings," he said.
