<HEADLINE> Pakistan Humiliates Bangladesh in Asia Cup Cricket </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh ended its seventh Asia Cup
Cricket campaign on Friday with the worst defeat in cricket's one-
day international history when Pakistan brushed aside the home
side by 233 runs to take sweet revenge of its World Cup loss, the
Independent newspaper reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The fourth match of the Asia Cup saw Bangladesh hitting the new
low in the history of one-day cricket, and it was also Bangladesh'
s lowest ever total, 87 runs against Pakistan's 320 runs, in its
40 one-day international cricket appearances.
</P>
<P>
"We played our worst game. The bowlers were below par and then
the batting itself was horrible," Bangladesh captain Bulbul said.
</P>
<P>
Former world champions Pakistan has never won the very
tournament, and the victory will keep it on course to change
history.
</P>
<P>
"Every player had in mind what happened during the World Cup
and everybody was very serious about this match," said Pakistan
captain Moin Khan.
</P>
<P>
In the last World Cup Cricket in Northampton, Bangladesh
surprisingly defeated mammoth Pakistan by 62 runs.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan will meet arch rivals India today in a crucial match.
India must win to keep it alive for a place in the final. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
