<HEADLINE> Croatia, Bosnia to Jointly Build Transport Corridor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Croatia and Bosnia-Herzegovina will
jointly build a land transportation corridor linking Croatia's
southern Polce port, the Bosnian capital of Sarajevo and the
Hungarian capital of Budapest.
</P>
<P>
Croatian Construction Minister Radomir Cacic and Bosnian
Foreign Trade and Economy Minister Mirsad Kurtovic Friday signed
an agreement on the project in Sarajevo, the Bosnian state news
agency BH Press reported.
</P>
<P>
Cacic was quoted as saying that the road is of special
importance to Croatia because it links southern Croatia and the
Slavonija region in northern Croatia by running through southern
Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
The road will also promote employment in Polce, which borders
Bosnia, he added.
</P>
<P>
Kurtovic said the corridor will provide the land-locked Bosnia
with an access to the Adriatic Sea, which is vital for the country
's foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the two countries are expected to start
preparations for the project in the near future, he said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also asked Hungary to participate in the project,
which will be submitted to a meeting of signatories to the
Southeastern Europe Stability Pact for discussions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
