<HEADLINE> Mexico Becomes Big Trading Partner With EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Mexico became the second
biggest trading partner with the European Union (EU) in Latin
America since it began to implement a free trade agreement with EU
last month, a report reaching here from Belgium said.
</P>
<P>
The report said that Mexico was the 24th biggest EU trading
partner in 1998, when the European exports to Mexico amounted to 9.
3 billion U.S. dollars and imports 4 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Brazil ranked the 12th biggest trading partner with the
European bloc in 1998, importing 15.5 billion dollars worth of
products to Europe and exporting 13.2 billion dollars, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat, the European Community statistics office, said that
the EU exports to Mexico increased from 4.5 billion dollars in
1995 to 10.4 billion dollars in 1999, while its imports from
Mexico jumped from 3.2 billion dollars in 1995 to 4.7 billion in
1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
