sciences.
</P>
<P>
China Stresses Importance of Technology in Afforestation
</P>
<P>
The State Forestry Administration of China has launched a
technology support program for anti-desertification engineering
projects in key areas.
</P>
<P>
Administration officials said the program will increase the
technical content of anti-desertification engineering projects,
improve the quality of these projects, and ensure a satisfactory
environmental impact.
</P>
<P>
In reaction to sand storms in the Beijing region, the
administration drafted a separate technology support program for
an afforestation project in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Scientists Develop Cells Killing Tumor
</P>
<P>
Chinese scientists announced that they have developed cells
which produce and secrete immune toxin to effectively kill tumor
cells.
</P>
<P>
Scientists from the Fourth Medical University of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army developed the cells by using genetic
recombination technology.
</P>
<P>
Through years of research, professor Yang Angang and his
colleagues found that T Lymphocytes can produce and secrete immune
toxins, while at the same time the growth and function of such
cells remains normal. 
</P>
