<HEADLINE> Sao Paulo Stocks Close Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, June 2 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on the Sao Paulo Securities
Exchange, the largest in Latin America, closed higher Friday with
the key Bovespa Index surging by 4.99 percent to 16,222 points
from Thursday's 15,450 points.
</P>
<P>
Dealers exchanged 703.8 million U.S. dollars against 483.2
million dollars in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate of the local currency, the real, stood at 1.
800 for one dollar, compared with Thursday's 1.818 for one dollars.
</P>
