<HEADLINE> Argentine Stocks Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 2 (Xinhua) -- The leading Merval index on
the Buenos Aires Exchange closed up 6.05 percent, at 501.37 points
on Friday against Thursday's 472.76 points.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 51.150 million dollars compared with 29.688
million dollars in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The annual inter-bank interest rate fell to 7.25 percent from 7.
50 percent on the 24-hour term. The exchange rate of the Argentine
peso against the U.S. dollar stood at 0.997 for purchase and 1.002
for sale. 
</P>
