<HEADLINE> Chelsea Seal 15 Million Pounds Hasselbaink Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Dutch striker Jimmy Floyd
Hasselbaink has completed a move back to the English Premiership
after Chelsea finally clinched a 15 million pounds deal with
Atletico Madrid.
</P>
<P>
Hasselbaink, who was surprisingly left out of Holland's Euro
2000 squad, has agreed personal terms.
</P>
<P>
The move makes the Dutchman the Blues' record signing, topping
the 10 million pounds they paid for Chris Sutton last summer.
</P>
<P>
The fee also matches the British transfer record paid by
Newcastle for Alan Shearer in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Hasselbaink said: "It's a very big move and I feel happy with
it.When I heard Chelsea were interested I was very pleased and
hoped the deal would go through."
</P>
<P>
"I enjoyed my time in English football and I am happy to be
back at a great club like Chelsea, who are very ambitious," he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
