<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Province Reports Brisk Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 3 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province, which
ranks third in the country in terms of gross domestic product,
generated 6.91 billion U.S. dollars from foreign trade during the
first four months of the year, an increase of 30.5 percent on a
yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
The total consists of 4.35 billion U.S. dollars of exports, up
31.7 percent, and 2.55 billion U.S. dollars of imports, up 28.6
percent.
</P>
<P>
Shandong's exports to Asia, Europe, America, Oceania and Africa
all grew during the January-April period.
</P>
<P>
Major export commodities include textiles, garments, farm
produce, furniture, machinery and electrical equipment.
</P>
<P>
Nationwide, China's foreign trade volume during the January-
April period totaled 137.1 billion U.S. dollars, a rise of 38.8
percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Imports of the country reached 64.9 billion U.S. dollars,
rising 38.6 percent, while exports were 72.2 billion U.S. dollars,
up 39 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
