<HEADLINE> Uruguay's GDP Up 0.4 Pct in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Uruguay's gross domestic product
(GDP) grew only 0.4 percent in the first quarter compared to the
same period of 1999, according to data published Saturday by the
Economy Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Uruguayan economy production data confirm that the 1999
recession has been surmounted, but reveal that the recovery
symptoms are not very noticeable.
</P>
<P>
The levels of activity in agriculture and construction
continued depressed, they recovered slightly in commerce and
industry, and transports and the growth was a little more evident
in transports and communications services.
</P>
<P>
The Uruguayan Economy Ministry said that official estimates
show that the GDP will advance from 2 percent to 2.5 percent this
year.
</P>
<P>
The only sectors of the economy that had a clear recovery
during the first quarter were electricity, gas, water, transports,
and communications.
</P>
<P>
Industry and trade linking to tourism also recovered during the
first quarter, although at a slower pace. 
</P>
</TEXT>
