<HEADLINE> Sinn Fein Condemns London Bridge Bombers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Sinn Fein's chief negotiator Martin
McGuinness Saturday warned dissident republicans not to start
attacking the British mainland following the Hammersmith Bridge
bombing.
</P>
<P>
The education minister in Northern Ireland's newly reinstated
power-sharing executive also condemned the bombers who damaged the
west London bridge Thursday.
</P>
<P>
No one has admitted responsibility for the attack but there
were fears that dissident republicans opposed to the Northern
Ireland peace process may have been involved.
</P>
<P>
The high-explosive device damaged the bridge but did not cause
any injuries.
</P>
<P>
McGuinness said all nationalists and republicans should respect
the wishes of the people to abide by the 1998 Good Friday
Agreement peace accord.
</P>
<P>
Sinn Fein was "totally and absolutely opposed" to the bombing,
he said, adding that "the overwhelming majority of nationalists
and republicans support the Sinn Fein leadership's efforts,
support the efforts of the SDLP and the Irish government."
</P>
<P>
Police investigating the blast were still trying to trace two
taxi drivers in the hope they may have clues which could lead to
the bombers.
</P>
<P>
Security in London has been stepped up as police confirmed the
sophisticated device contained between 1kg and 2kg of high
explosives and was fully detonated.
</P>
<P>
The police have urged members of the public to be vigilant and
have not ruled out the possibility that the attack was carried out
by dissident republicans.
</P>
<P>
Scotland Yard said its officers were investigating a claim made
to a media outlet in Belfast that the blast was the work of the
dissident republican Continuity IRA.
</P>
<P>
Ulster Unionist deputy leader John Taylor said dissident
republicans trying to destabilize the peace process could have
been behind the blast.
</P>
<P>
If dissident republicans were involved, then this would be the
first time they have launched an attack in mainland Britain.
</P>
</TEXT>
