<HEADLINE> Colombian Inflation Up 0.5 Pct </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Colombian inflation index rose 0.
5 percent in May because of rises in the transport, health,
housing, and communications sectors, the National Statistics
Administrative Department (DANE) said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
DANE Director Rene Verswyvel said that the variation recorded
last month "cannot be explained by pressure in food at a
difference with previous months and against the general perception.
"
</P>
<P>
On the contrary, Verswyvel said that the rises in transport,
housing, and communications are 80 percent of the total inflation
increase.
</P>
<P>
Inflation accumulated from January 1 to May 31 is seven percent,
0.75 percent more than the rate in the same period of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, annual inflation amounts to 10 percent against 9.98
percent for the same period of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Verswyvel said that a drop in the family basket cost is
expected in the next months, after the first five months of the
year, when the cost of living registers the biggest rises.
</P>
</TEXT>
