<HEADLINE> Moderate Earthquake Hits Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.3 degrees on
the Richter scale alarmed the population of Chimbote, a city
located north of Lima, the Peruvian Geophysical Institute (IGP)
reported Saturday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The press release of the IGP said that the seism did not cause
material or human damage in the towns that surround the fishing
city of Chimbote.
</P>
<P>
The IGP said that the epicenter of the tremor, which occurred
at 11:20 local time, was 32 kilometers west of Chimbote and was
also felt south of the Ancash department.
</P>
<P>
It said that the occurrence of light quakes is common and that
they occur in Chimbote and Casma with some regularity because
those zones are on the Oceanica and Nazca tectonic plates, which
present a geography in continuous state of change.  
</P>
</TEXT>
