<HEADLINE> Snow Closes North of Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Over one meter deep snow remains
accumulated in the mountain range sectors of the Chilean Second
Region (Antofagasta), cutting the mountain passages of Jama and
Sico.
</P>
<P>
The Regional Emergency Office said Saturday that several
vehicles were trapped in the sector in the last hours.
</P>
<P>
The same situation occurs on the Argentine side, where a bus
that was going to Chile had a mechanical breakdown caused by the
snow. Low temperatures have affected the Antofagasta City
residents.
</P>
<P>
The bad weather caused a fatal victim and 713 persons were
affected in the south.
</P>
<P>
The cold and snow affect the southern zone of the country,
between the Eighth and the Eleventh Regions. A state of alert is
maintained in the Ninth Region (La Araucania) because of the
strong wind and rain that have not abated during the last hours,
and that continue causing havoc, especially in Temuco.
</P>
<P>
Seventy kilometers per hour squalls have been recorded in
Temuco Saturday morning, while the rains have created pools that
impede the normal movement of vehicles and pedestrians.
</P>
<P>
One of the most affected sectors is that of Padre Las Casas,
where Carabinero (uniformed police) agents have had to rescue
people stranded by the storm.
</P>
<P>
The Emergency National Office (ONEMI) said that the situations
of urgency are being cared for by the respective municipalities
and by the Regional Emergency Directions. The ONEMI sent to the
zone a mobile center of emergency operations and technical
personnel to support the evaluation and operative coordination.
</P>
</TEXT>
